        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Gather round and let's begin with a quick history lesson because in this case, the context really helps… The ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Moto Roader",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " games, it turns out, were a trilogy of top-down racing games released on NEC’s oft-forgotten TurboGrafx-16 console (also known as the PC Engine) in the late 80s/early 90s. Some of you may be familiar with the series, seeing how it made some sporadic appearances on the Wii/Wii U Virtual Consoles over the years; ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Moto Roader MC",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " was the third and final game in the trilogy originally released in 1992, and now, 30 years on, has somehow found its way onto the Nintendo Switch.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s6GeFULGOPA",
        "html": "<iframe width=\"200\" height=\"113\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/s6GeFULGOPA?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>",
        "metadata": {
          "title": "Moto Roader MC - Out Now!",
          "author_name": "Ratalaika Games",
          "author_url": "https://www.youtube.com/c/RatalaikaGames",
          "height": 113,
          "width": 200,
          "version": "1.0",
          "provider_name": "YouTube",
          "provider_url": "https://www.youtube.com/",
          "thumbnail_height": 360,
          "thumbnail_width": 480,
          "thumbnail_url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/s6GeFULGOPA/hqdefault.jpg"
        },
        "embedType": "video"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Good",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Overall, I have to say the gameplay is pretty fun once you get the hang of the controls. The single player mode involves you racing against four other NPCs on a variety of colourful tracks, all of which fit onto the Switch’s screen in their entirety. Similar to the Grand Prixs in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Mario Kart",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", you’re awarded with a number of points depending on where you finished in the race. Then, after a number of races (usually around five races in any given Grand Prix), you of course are placed on the overall leaderboard and you better be on the top step! As well as trying to outpace your rivals, you are armed with some handy rockets and pipe bombs which you can use to blast them away. The combat is probably the most fun aspect of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Moto Roader MC",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " as it leads to some crazy first corner pile-ups with cars heading in all directions and rockets flying everywhere!",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "html",
        "html": "<a href=\"https://powera.pxf.io/c/3324894/1309898/15385\" target=\"_top\" id=\"1309898\"><img src=\"//a.impactradius-go.com/display-ad/15385-1309898\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"728\" height=\"90\"/></a><img height=\"0\" width=\"0\" src=\"https://imp.pxf.io/i/3324894/1309898/15385\" style=\"position:absolute;visibility:hidden;\" border=\"0\" />"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The single player got quite tedious pretty quickly but the multiplayer is a lot more fun. Racing against your mates is a lot more engrossing than against the NPCs, whose AI is quite basic. There’s also a mode called Omake which is basically ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Rocket League",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " but 1 on 1 and 2D, however it is bloody-good fun!",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "TL;DR",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Chaotic and fun racing action",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
